---
import LegalLayout from '../components/LegalLayout.astro';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How WellPeps collects, uses, shares, and protects your personal information."
>
  <p class="legal__meta">
    Effective Date: <span class="ph">[CLIENT: production launch date]</span><br />
    Last Updated: <span class="ph">[CLIENT: same as effective date for v1]</span>
  </p>

  <p>
    This Privacy Policy describes how
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: exact legal entity name]</span> (&ldquo;WellPeps,&rdquo;
    &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us&rdquo;) collects, uses, discloses, and protects personal
    information when you visit our website, create an account, or use our services.
  </p>
  <div class="callout--note callout">
    <strong>Scope note — two privacy documents apply</strong>
    <p>
      Protected health information handled in connection with medical care is governed by the
      <a href="/notice-of-privacy-practices">Notice of Privacy Practices</a> under HIPAA. This
      Privacy Policy covers everything else — website visits, marketing, account data, and
      information collected before a provider relationship exists.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <h3>Information you provide</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Identity and contact details: name, email, phone number, date of birth, shipping and billing address;</li>
    <li>Account credentials;</li>
    <li>Health intake information you submit before or during the consultation process;</li>
    <li>Payment information (processed by our payment processor — we do not store full card numbers);</li>
    <li>Communications with our support team, and survey or review responses.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Information collected automatically</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Device and browser information, IP address, and approximate location;</li>
    <li>Usage data: pages viewed, links clicked, referring pages, session duration;</li>
    <li>Cookies and similar technologies, as described in Section 5.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To provide, operate, and improve the platform and connect you with providers and pharmacies;</li>
    <li>To process payments, subscriptions, and shipments;</li>
    <li>To communicate with you about your account, orders, and service updates;</li>
    <li>To send marketing communications, where permitted and subject to your opt-out rights;</li>
    <li>To detect and prevent fraud, abuse, and security incidents;</li>
    <li>To comply with legal obligations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. How We Share Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Healthcare providers and pharmacies</strong> — to deliver the services you request;</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Service providers</strong> — vendors that host, process payments, ship orders, send
      communications, and provide analytics on our behalf, under contracts limiting their use of
      your data. <span class="ph">[CLIENT: provide the full vendor list — hosting, payments, EHR/telehealth platform, pharmacy integrations, email/SMS, analytics]</span>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Legal and safety</strong> — when required by law, legal process, or to protect rights and safety;</li>
    <li><strong>Business transfers</strong> — in connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets, with notice to you.</li>
  </ul>
  <div class="callout">
    <strong>Open item — do we &ldquo;sell or share&rdquo; personal information?</strong>
    <p>
      Whether WellPeps &ldquo;sells&rdquo; or &ldquo;shares&rdquo; personal information under
      CCPA/CPRA depends on the advertising tags on the site. The client must supply a complete
      cookie and pixel inventory (GA4, Meta Pixel, TikTok, etc.). Advertising pixels on a
      health-services site are the single riskiest item in this document — several FTC enforcement
      actions have targeted exactly this. Until inventoried, this policy cannot truthfully say
      &ldquo;we do not sell or share.&rdquo;
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>4. Consumer Health Data</h2>
  <p>
    Some states (including Washington under the My Health My Data Act, and Nevada) give consumer
    health data specific protections outside HIPAA. To the extent those laws apply, we collect and
    share consumer health data only with your consent or as necessary to provide services you
    request, and you may exercise the rights described in Section 7.
    <span class="ph">[COUNSEL: confirm MHMDA applicability and whether a separate Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy link is required for Washington residents]</span>
  </p>

  <h2>5. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
  <p>
    We use cookies and similar technologies for essential site functions, preferences, analytics,
    and — if enabled — advertising.
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: final cookie table pending the tag inventory: name, provider, purpose, duration for each]</span>
    You can control cookies through your browser settings, and opt out of any
    advertising-related sharing via <a href="/your-privacy-choices">Your Privacy Choices</a>. We
    honor Global Privacy Control (GPC) signals where required by law.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Data Retention and Security</h2>
  <p>
    We retain personal information for as long as needed for the purposes described above:
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: retention periods for account data, health intake data, and marketing data]</span>.
    We use administrative, technical, and physical safeguards appropriate to the sensitivity of the
    data, including encryption in transit and at rest, access controls, and vendor security review.
    No system is perfectly secure; we will notify you of a breach as required by law.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your state, you may have the right to know what personal information we hold about
    you, access it, correct it, delete it, receive a portable copy, opt out of sale/sharing and
    targeted advertising, and limit the use of sensitive personal information. We will not
    discriminate against you for exercising these rights.
  </p>
  <p>To exercise any right:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Visit <a href="/your-privacy-choices">Your Privacy Choices</a>;</li>
    <li>Email <span class="ph">[CLIENT: privacy contact — privacy@wellpeps.com recommended]</span>;</li>
    <li>Call <a href="tel:+18339357377">(833) 935-7377</a>.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We will verify your request using the information associated with your account and respond
    within the time required by your state&rsquo;s law (45 days in most states, extendable once).
    You may use an authorized agent, subject to verification.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Children</h2>
  <p>
    Our services are intended for adults. We do not knowingly collect personal information from
    anyone under 18. If you believe a minor has provided us information, contact us and we will
    delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We will post updates to this page and revise the &ldquo;Last Updated&rdquo; date. For material
    changes, we will provide additional notice by
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: notice method — email and/or site banner]</span>.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: legal entity name]</span><br />
    Attn: Privacy — <span class="ph">[CLIENT: privacy officer name or title]</span><br />
    <span class="ph">[CLIENT: registered business address]</span><br />
    Email: <span class="ph">[CLIENT: privacy contact email]</span> &nbsp;|&nbsp; Phone:
    <a href="tel:+18339357377">(833) 935-7377</a>
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
